# Track the INTRANUKE pion cross-section text tables needed by the pure-Python
# pion-FSI reweighting (src/pion_fsi_reweighting.py) -- the rest of the GENIE
# build stays ignored.  Re-include the path one level at a time (git can't
# un-ignore a file whose parent dir is ignored), then the 5 data dirs the
# calculator actually reads: the 2025 cross-section tables and the 2018 fraction
# tables (pipA_{cex,abs,inelas,pipro}_frac).
!BuildEventGenerators/Generator/
BuildEventGenerators/Generator/*
!BuildEventGenerators/Generator/data/
BuildEventGenerators/Generator/data/*
!BuildEventGenerators/Generator/data/evgen/
BuildEventGenerators/Generator/data/evgen/*
!BuildEventGenerators/Generator/data/evgen/intranuke/
BuildEventGenerators/Generator/data/evgen/intranuke/*
!BuildEventGenerators/Generator/data/evgen/intranuke/tot_xsec/
BuildEventGenerators/Generator/data/evgen/intranuke/tot_xsec/*
!BuildEventGenerators/Generator/data/evgen/intranuke/tot_xsec/2025/
!BuildEventGenerators/Generator/data/evgen/intranuke/tot_xsec/pipA_cex_frac/
!BuildEventGenerators/Generator/data/evgen/intranuke/tot_xsec/pipA_abs_frac/
!BuildEventGenerators/Generator/data/evgen/intranuke/tot_xsec/pipA_inelas_frac/
!BuildEventGenerators/Generator/data/evgen/intranuke/tot_xsec/pipA_pipro_frac/


ubana/
ubsim/
